This implementation of word count makes use of the Scanner delimiter to split words.
The delimiter pattern splits text such as "hello? 'hello'" into the words: hello hello

An assumption is made that the text is gramatically correct.

This project was created in VSCode with the Java Extension Pack
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/languages/java

Test files are included which test the program on the given example, extreme 
punctuation examples, and numbers.